Describe a song you liked when you were a child
- What it is
- When you heard of it
- What it was about
- Explain why you liked it when you were a child

I'm going to talk about "Old McDonald Had a Farm", which is a song I really loved when I was a child.

I don’t remember exactly when I first heard it, but it must have been many years ago, probably when I was very young. At that time, my mother wanted me to get more exposure to English, so she often played playlists of popular English songs for children. Among those, this song quickly became one of my favorites.

The song is about an old farmer named McDonald who owns a farm and raises various kinds of animals. Throughout the song, each animal is introduced along with its unique sound, which makes it fun and easy for children to recognize and imitate them.

There are several reasons why I enjoyed listening to this song when I was a child. First of all, it has a very catchy tune and a simple, repetitive rhythm, which makes it extremely fun and easy to sing along to. After a long day at school, when I was often overwhelmed with homework, I would come home and sing or even dance along to the song whenever it was played. It really helped me relax and clear my mind.

In addition, the song introduced me to useful English vocabulary, especially the names and sounds of common animals, which I found both interesting and memorable. In a way, it even sparked my interest in learning English more seriously later on.

Nowadays, I don’t listen to this song very often since I’ve grown up. However, whenever I hear it again, especially when I’m with my nieces or nephews, it brings back a lot of childhood memories. Interestingly, the last time I searched for this song on YouTube, it had already reached more than 6 billion views. I believe this number will continue to rise, as the song is still loved by children all over the world.
